1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Grasping is a skill family, not one hand pose.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Taxonomy names grasp styles, but task purpose selects useful ones.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Closure turns grasp purpose into a testable condition.

4
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Three prepared grasp agents cover distinct closure strategies.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Contact-web agents make grasp structure explicit.

6
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Superquadrics provide a compact shape representation.

7
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:21,000
CNN and RL training connect perceived shape to grasp action.

8
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:31,000
One grasp agent can handle many object shapes.

9
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Force strategy becomes part of the agent interface.
